.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "May 2026" "Holberton School" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter written in C.

The shell reads commands from standard input, parses the command into arguments,
searches for the executable file in the PATH environment variable, and executes
the command using system calls such as fork, execve, and wait.

The shell works in both interactive mode and non-interactive mode.

.SH OPTIONS
This shell does not support command line options.

.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
In interactive mode, the shell displays a prompt and waits for the user to enter
a command.

Example:

.B
./hsh

Then type:

.B
ls

.SH NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
In non-interactive mode, commands can be passed to the shell through a pipe.

Example:

.B
echo "ls" | ./hsh

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS

.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.

.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLES

.TP
Run the shell:
.B
./hsh

.TP
List files:
.B
ls

.TP
List files using full path:
.B
/bin/ls

.TP
Print the current working directory:
.B
pwd

.TP
Print environment variables:
.B
env

.TP
Exit the shell:
.B
exit

.TP
Use non-interactive mode:
.B
echo "ls" | ./hsh

.SH FILES

.TP
.B shell.c
Contains the main shell loop, input reading, parsing, built-ins, and command
execution logic.

.TP
.B path.c
Contains functions used to search for commands in the PATH.

.TP
.B main.h
Contains function prototypes, included libraries, and external variables.

.TP
.B README.md
Contains project documentation.

.TP
.B AUTHORS
Contains the list of project contributors.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell exits with the status of the executed command.

If a command is not found, the shell may return an error status.

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

